<P>But it is needlesse he<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"><NOTE PLACE="marg">But A|theists ra|ther in this age are to be encoun|tred with, pretending Faith which they haue not.</NOTE> to encounter with <HI>Ar<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">|ans;</HI> their heresie is burie<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> and I will not open th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> Sepulchre to offend th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> Saints of God with th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> loathsome and stinkin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> smell thereof. I wish th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> age were as quyt of A|theists, who come to th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> Church as <HI>Achab</HI> we<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> to the Campe, changing their garment, but no<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> their heart. Euery ma<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">
