<P><PB N="134" REF="72">The doctrine of th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"><NOTE PLACE="marg">Comfort|lesse is the doctrine of the church of Rome co~cerning&punc; death.</NOTE> Stepmother-Church o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> Rome comes far short o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> this comfort: the deat<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> of her children they call<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> downe-going to an hou<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> in hell, to wit, <HI>Purgatory</HI> not an vpgoing to our fa|thers house in heauen&punc; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word"> comfortles religion&punc; Phi|sitians are they of no va|lue: miserable are the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> who are blinded by them Their religion tells the that in thy life-time tho<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> canst not be sure of salua|tion, and in death it as|sures thee thou must g<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> into purgatory, the pain<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> wherof differeth nothing
