<P>With <HI>Augustine</HI> agreeth<NOTE PLACE="marg">With <HI>Au|gustine</HI> agreeth <HI>Bernard. Ierem.</HI> 1. 5.</NOTE> <HI>Bernard:</HI> I read, saies he, that the Lord spake of <HI>Ie|remie, Before thou came out of the wombe, I sanctified thee:</HI> And of <HI>Iohn</HI> the <HI>Bap|tist, Qui ex viero, Domi|num in vtero sensit,</HI> who in the womb of his owne Mother <HI>Elizabeth</HI> was touched with a feeling of his Lord, in the wombe of <HI>Marie</HI> the blessed Vir|gin;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Bern. Epist. 174.</NOTE> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="2 words"> had fallen out (<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">ee) that any of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="2 words"> died in the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word">, meaning of <HI>Ie|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"></HI> or <HI>Iohn,</HI> who will
