our nature in that con|quered<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 In posses|sing vs in these man|sions pla|ces. <HI>Tertul. de resur. carnis.</HI></NOTE> Kingdome. O<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> this <HI>Tertullian,</HI> in name o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> all the Saints, gloryeth i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> this manner: <HI>Quemadmo|dum nobis aharabonem Spi|ritus reliquit, ita &agrave; nobis a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">|rabonem carnis accepit, &amp; vexit in Coelum pignus to|tius summae illuc quando<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> redigendae: Securae esto<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> caro &amp; sanguis, vsurpast<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> enim Coelum &amp; Regnum Dei in Christo:</HI> As t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> Lord hath left behind him vnto vs, the earne<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> of his Spirit, so hath h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> taken fro~ vs the earnest <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> our flesh, &amp; carried it in<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> heauen, as a pledge th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">
