<PB N="171" REF="90">
Apostle vseth not the word <GAP DESC="foreign">, which signi|fieth<NOTE PLACE="marg">The diffe|rence of the words <GAP DESC="foreign"> and <GAP DESC="foreign">, declares the way was open then albe|it not so cleare as now.</NOTE> to open that which was closed, but hee vseth the word <GAP DESC="foreign">, which signifieth to make mani|fest and cleare a thing which is darke and ob|scure. Now there is a great difference betweene these two; to say that the way of heauen was ob|scured with shadowes &amp; couerings, which were re|moued by Christs com|ming, and the way to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">eauen more clearly ma|nifested; and to say, that the way and dore of hea|uen was closed &amp; locked
